    • Method Detail

      • getTransmissionTransferID

        public static java.lang.String getTransmissionTransferID(java.lang.String transferID)
        Given a transfer ID string of "TransmissionTransferID;DocDBTransferID", return the "TransmissionTransferID" (i.e., classic/original transfer ID) portion. If no semicolon is found, and the string is not a UUID pattern, then the string is assumed to be the TransmissionTransferID.
        Parameters:
        transferID - the transfer ID string of form "TransmissionTransferID;DocDBTransferID".
        Returns:
        the TransmissionTransferID. Returns empty string if not present (or if input string is null).

      • getTransmissionTransferID

        public static java.lang.String getTransmissionTransferID(java.lang.String transferID,
                                                         boolean withSemicolon)
        Given a transfer ID string of "TransmissionTransferID;DocDBTransferID", return the "TransmissionTransferID" (i.e., classic/original transfer ID) portion. If no semicolon is found, and the string is not a UUID pattern, then the string is assumed to be the TransmissionTransferID.
        Parameters:
        transferID - the transfer ID string of form "TransmissionTransferID;DocDBTransferID".
        withSemicolon - if true, returns "TransmissionTransferID;". If false, returns only "TransmissionTransferID".
        Returns:
        the TransmissionTransferID. Returns empty string if not present (or if input string is null).

      • getDocDBTransferID

        public static java.lang.String getDocDBTransferID(java.lang.String transferID)
        Given a transfer ID string of "TransmissionTransferID;DocDBTransferID", return the "DocDBTransferID" (i.e., the UUID transfer ID) portion. If no semicolon is found, and the string matches a UUID pattern, then the string is assumed to be the DocDBTransferID.
        Parameters:
        transferID - the transfer ID string of form "TransmissionTransferID;DocDBTransferID".
        Returns:
        the DocDBTransferID. Returns empty string if not present (or if input string is null).

      • getDocDBTransferID

        public static java.lang.String getDocDBTransferID(java.lang.String transferID,
                                                  boolean withSemicolon)
        Given a transfer ID string of "TransmissionTransferID;DocDBTransferID", return the "DocDBTransferID" (i.e., the UUID transfer ID) portion. If no semicolon is found, and the string matches a UUID pattern, then the string is assumed to be the DocDBTransferID.
        Parameters:
        transferID - the transfer ID string of form "TransmissionTransferID;DocDBTransferID".
        withSemicolon - if true, returns ";DocDBTransferID". If false, returns only "DocDBTransferID".
        Returns:
        the DocDBTransferID. Returns empty string if not present (or if input string is null).
